title: Ursula & Mickey | AHS: Double Feature - Episode 3: "Thirst" (HQ Clip)
author: AHS Crave
comment: I am really loving Leslie Grossman's character this season. Also why wasn't TB Karen on tonight's episode?
yeah this is leslies best character and most natural performance. she really steals the show this episode

I don't understand why Ryan keeps making Leslie's characters bitchy and shady. You can tell this woman has range and I would love for her to play more mature and dramatic roles like episode 1-5 Margaret last season
leslie's third role in AHS is another rich girl🙂
1:10 When a guy won't stop talking to you (also when you're a lesbian)
description: "Thirst", the third episode of American Horror Story: Double Feature (Part 1 - Red Tide) - written by Brad Falchuk, directed by Loni Peristere - stars Sarah Paulson as Tuberculosis Karen, Evan Peters as Austin Sommers, Lily Rabe as Doris Gardener, Finn Wittrock as Harry Gardener, Ryan Kiera Armstrong as Alma Gardener, Frances Conroy as Belle Noir, Billie Lourd as Lark, Leslie Grossman as Ursula, Adina Porter as Chief Burelson, Angelica Ross as The Chemist, Macaulay Culkin as Mickey, Denis O'Hare as Holden, and Robin Weigert as Martha.
